- content_for :title, "About wdiffer"

#about
  %h1
    = link_to 'wdiffer', :root

  #wdiffer
    %h2
      About wdiffer
    %p
      wdiffer is a simple web tool to compare
      %span
        = surround('(', ',') do
          = link_to '"diff"', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diff_utility'
      in computer slang) words in two chunks of text by words. It's named after (and functionally almost equivalent to) the GNU tool
      %span
        = succeed('.') do
          = link_to 'wdiff', 'http://www.gnu.org/software/wdiff/'

  #history
    %h2
      History
    %p
      The use case I had in mind I built this little page is
      %span
        = succeed('.') do
          = link_to "Bible memorization", "http://www.desiringgod.org/blog/posts/ten-reasons-to-memorize-big-chunks-of-the-bible"
      I built this in December 2014 when my fianc√©e was traveling with family and hard to contact. We had been memorizing the book of
      %span
        = link_to 'Colossians', 'http://esv.literalword.com/?q=col+1-4'
      together and I wanted a way to test myself more accurately while we weren't able to test each other.
    %p
      There are other similar tools out there but I found them to be cluttery, hard to use, or lacking features.

  #contact
    %h2
      Contact

    %p
      Please feel free to
      %span
        = link_to 'contact me', 'http://www.jasontku.com/contact/'
      to report bugs and suggest features or improvements. Specifically, if you are a design-minded person who wants to help make this app not look so ugly, please do reach out.


